<h1>Confirm</h1>

<p>
A confirmation modal with 'Yes' and 'No' buttons
</p>
<p>
When 'No' is pressed the modal just get closed, while if the 'Yes' button is pressed an action named <i>confirm</i> is invoked on the controller, giving the controller the opportunity to decide whether to close the modal or not.
</p>

<h2>Demo</h2>

{{em-modal-confirm confirm-id="m" configName="bs" close-if=close}}
{{#em-modal-toggler modal-id="m"}}Delete{{/em-modal-toggler}}

<h2>Markup</h2>
<div class="well line-example"><pre><code class="handlebars">\{{em-modal-confirm confirm-id="m" configName="bs" close-if=close}}
&lt;!--<i>modal-id</i> is set to the value of the modal's <i>confirm-id</i> property--&gt;
\{{#em-modal-toggler modal-id="m"}}Delete\{{/em-modal-toggler}}
</code></pre></div>

<div class="well line-example"><pre><code class="coffeescript">Ember.Controller.extend
    close: false
    actions:
        confirm: ->
            alert "Confirmed!"
            @set 'close', true
</code></pre></div>